{
  "name": "Multisport",
  "overview": "Multisport is a racing competition that includes any combination of running, biking, or swimming. This badge serves as a natural progression for Scouts who are interested in or have earned individual badges for Swimming, Cycling, Athletics, or Personal Fitness. For Scouts active in one of these sports, it provides a fun opportunity to expand into another fitness area and enjoy the benefits of cross-training. Scouts proficient in two sports can discover new ways to combine their skills, which offers both immediate and long-term benefits for well-being, personal growth, and athletic endeavors.",
  "is_eagle_required": false,
  "is_lab": false,
  "url": "https://www.scouting.org/merit-badges/multisport/",
  "pdf_url": "https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Multisport.pdf",
  "workbook_pdf_url": null,
  "workbook_docx_url": null,
  "shop_url": "https://www.scoutshop.org/multisport-merit-badge-pamphlet-664475.html",
  "image_url": "https://www.scouting.org/wp-content/uploads/elementor/thumbs/image-2025-02-27-09-43-04-538-r26gpo6c0hzm8tgjjbeeisdddwme7gixvndbpjfskg.png",
  "image_filename": "multisport-merit-badge.jpg",
  "requirements": [
    {
      "id": "14960",
      "label": "1",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Do the following:"
        }
      ],
      "resources": [],
      "sub_requirements": [
        {
          "id": "14961",
          "label": "a",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Explain to your counselor the most likely hazards you may encounter during multisport activities and what you should do to anticipate, prevent, mitigate, and respond to these hazards."
            }
          ],
          "resources": [
            {
              "title": "How To Avoid Injury When Triathlon Training (video)",
              "url": "https://youtu.be/LckcSB-O8UI"
            }
          ],
          "sub_requirements": []
        },
        {
          "id": "14962",
          "label": "b",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Show that you know first aid for injuries or illnesses that could occur while participating in multisport events, including abrasions, blisters, concussions, contusions, dehydration, hypothermia, overheating, sprains, and strains."
            }
          ],
          "resources": [
            {
              "title": "R.I.C.E. Treatment for Sprains and Strains (video)",
              "url": "https://youtu.be/TZqDBgiEfL8"
            },
            {
              "title": "Treating Heat Exhaustion and Heat Stroke (video)",
              "url": "https://youtu.be/5hSpMdlXZw0"
            },
            {
              "title": "How To Avoid and Treat Foot Blisters (video)",
              "url": "https://youtu.be/H6xlECl9ZBg"
            }
          ],
          "sub_requirements": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "14963",
      "label": "2",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Do the following:"
        }
      ],
      "resources": [],
      "sub_requirements": [
        {
          "id": "14964",
          "label": "a",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Discuss the importance of having a physical examination each year. Discuss why overall health, immunizations, medications, allergies, and medical history are covered during an examination. Tell your counselor when you last underwent a physical examination."
            }
          ],
          "resources": [
            {
              "title": "Scouting America Annual Health and Medical Record (website)",
              "url": "https://www.scouting.org/health-and-safety/ahmr/"
            }
          ],
          "sub_requirements": []
        },
        {
          "id": "14965",
          "label": "b",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Explain the importance of maintaining good health habits, especially during training, and how the use of tobacco products, alcohol, and other harmful substances can negatively affect your health and your performance in athletic activities."
            }
          ],
          "resources": [
            {
              "title": "7 Reasons To Be Smoke-Free (video)",
              "url": "https://youtu.be/hCC1dgmwO_4"
            },
            {
              "title": "Vaping Impacts Your Athletic Ability (video)",
              "url": "https://youtu.be/zXL9k-rJvIo"
            },
            {
              "title": "3 Things To Know About Drinking Alcohol (video)",
              "url": "https://youtu.be/YbBIl2KcVIQ"
            }
          ],
          "sub_requirements": []
        },
        {
          "id": "14966",
          "label": "c",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Define a healthy diet and explain the importance of maintaining a healthy diet."
            }
          ],
          "resources": [
            {
              "title": "Nutrition Fuels Training! (video)",
              "url": "https://youtu.be/zMposrWrPC0"
            }
          ],
          "sub_requirements": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "14967",
      "label": "3",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Do the following:"
        }
      ],
      "resources": [],
      "sub_requirements": [
        {
          "id": "14968",
          "label": "a",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Discuss with your counselor your level of familiarity and experience with the multisport events (swimming, biking, and running) and the order and distance of each sports segment."
            }
          ],
          "resources": [
            {
              "title": "Empowering Youth Through Multisport (video)",
              "url": "https://youtu.be/qmW51zdyduc"
            }
          ],
          "sub_requirements": []
        },
        {
          "id": "14969",
          "label": "b",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Explain to your counselor which multisport event (swimming, biking, or running) you feel is your strongest and which you could improve upon the most."
            }
          ],
          "resources": [
            {
              "title": "Multisport Disciplines (website)",
              "url": "https://www.usatriathlon.org/multisport/disciplines%20"
            }
          ],
          "sub_requirements": []
        },
        {
          "id": "14970",
          "label": "c",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Identify the required equipment for each of the three common multisport events (swimming, biking, and running)."
            }
          ],
          "resources": [
            {
              "title": "USA Triathlon Youth Guide (PDF)",
              "url": "https://assets.contentstack.io/v3/assets/blteb7d012fc7ebef7f/blteec8160c769bfc2e/648b54b80f2d9bd22bed580b/USAT_Youth_Guide_2019.pdf"
            },
            {
              "title": "Triathlon Equipment You Really Need (video)",
              "url": "https://youtu.be/kgbz_3B9dNA"
            }
          ],
          "sub_requirements": []
        },
        {
          "id": "14971",
          "label": "d",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Based on your interests, experience, and discussion with your counselor, select ONE of the following multisport formats to concentrate on for the remaining requirements: triathlon (swimming, biking, and running), duathlon (biking and running), aquathlon (swimming and running), or aquabike (swimming and biking)."
            }
          ],
          "resources": [],
          "sub_requirements": []
        }
      ]
    },
